comments: Murray (DEN) initiates body and arm contact with Davis (LAL), affecting the layup attempt.
James (LAL) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Davis (LAL) engages and disengages with Murray (DEN) off-ball, and marginal contact occurs as Murray moves to set the screen.
Murray's (DEN) hands slightly extend forward when he establishes himself in Hachimura's (LAL) path and he absorbs the marginal contact as he sets the screen.
James (LAL) and Davis (LAL) each bring their hands toward Jokic's (DEN) left and right side, respectively, and marginal contact occurs as Jokic drives toward the lane.
Hachimura (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away as Jokic (DEN) attempts to make the pass.
After the ball is cleanly dislodged by Hachimura's (LAL) arm during the pass attempt, the ball deflects off of Hachimura's right leg and Hachimura does not intentionally kick it.
Davis (LAL) is moving alongside Jokic's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs with Jokic's side as Jokic simultaneously loses control of the ball on his own during the drive.
Davis (LAL) rests his hand momentarily against Jokic's (DEN) side and marginal contact occurs as Jokic fades away toward the sideline during his upward shooting motion.
Correctly called shot clock violation on Denver.
Gordon (DEN) wraps his left arm around Davis' (LAL) midsection and affects Davis' FOM as he rolls toward the lane.
Schroder (LAL) is moving alongside Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) path and marginal side-to-side contact occurs as Caldwell-Pope moves toward the top of the perimeter.
James (LAL) engages and disengages with Caldwell-Pope (DEN) at the top of the perimeter, and marginal contact occurs as Caldwell-Pope sets the pick.
James (LAL) places his hand momentarily to Jokic's (DEN) front and slides his hand off as he begins to roll.
Murray (DEN) avoids stepping out of bounds as he dribbles along the sideline.
Davis (LAL) maintains a rested left hand on Murray's (DEN) right side and marginal contact occurs prior to Murray losing his balance on his own at the end of the drive.
Hachimura (LAL) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Gordon (DEN) and simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Gordon's side as the pass is made.

Possession is awarded to Denver. However, the ball touches Murray's (DEN) left hand last before going out of bounds. Reaves does not make contact with it. Possession should have been awarded to Los Angeles.
Davis (LAL) grasps and then quickly releases Jokic's (DEN) jersey during the drive, and further marginal body contact occurs prior to Jokic's gather.
Davis (LAL) and Schroder (LAL) each move forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Jokic (DEN) after Jokic's gather.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Gordon (DEN) engages and disengages with James (LAL), and marginal contact occurs as James moves over the screen.
Schroder (LAL) establishes himself in Gordon's (DEN) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Gordon (DEN) brings his hands toward James' (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs as James turns to start his drive.
Gordon (DEN) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) gathers the rebound on his right foot and takes two legal steps before coming to a stop along the baseline.

Porter Jr. (DEN) did not gain possession of the rebound before to the expiration of the shot clock, and a shot clock violation was warranted.  [This comment amended from the original posting for clarity.]
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) maintains his left foot as his pivot as he starts his dribble.
Davis (LAL) engages and disengages with Jokic (DEN), and marginal contact occurs as Jokic moves to set the pick.
Schroder (LAL) brings his hands toward Murray's (DEN) back/side and marginal contact occurs as Murray turns back toward the lane near the block.
Murray (DEN) brings his off-arm toward Schroder's (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs as Schroder defends in the post.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Murray's (DEN) floater attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) makes contact with the ball as simultaneous incidental arm contact occurs with James (LAL) during the rebound.

Murray (DEN) uses both hands to make clean contact with the ball after James' (LAL) gather. Gordon is aligning to move alongside James' (LAL) path and marginal body contact occurs prior to Gordon cleanly blocking the driving shot attempt.
Murray (DEN) makes contact with the ball and the part of James' (LAL) hand that is on the ball, dislodging it away from James during the rebound.
